full-fledged alliance. It is solid and comprehensive and continues to show a consistent incremental upward trend. There are strong structural incentives for furthering the China-Russia alignment, and there is little that might hinder the effective functioning of a China-Russia alliance. The alignment framework developed in the book can be applied to other cases of interstate strategic cooperation to facilitate comparisons between different strategic alignments.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 0aWorld politics. 4aAsian Studies. 4aChina. 4aContemporary Society. 4aEast Asia and North East Asia. 4aInternational Relations. 4aInternational relations. 4aPolitical science and theory. 4aPolitics and Government. 4aRussia. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh  aAlignment, strategic cooperation, China-Russia relations.1 aKorolev, Alexander, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076709408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2z978311076700108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2022 Englishz978311099451308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2022z9783110994407oZDB-23-PLW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048552733?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048552733423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048552733/original  a978-3-11-076700-1  DG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2b2022  a9